6:
I was angry with my people; I defiled my heritage\q1 and gave them over into your hand, but you showed them no mercy;
\q1 you placed a very heavy yoke on the old people.

\q1

8:
So now hear this, you who love pleasure and sit securely;\q1 you who say in your heart, "I exist, and there is no one else like me;
\q1 I will never sit as a widow, nor will I ever experience loss of children."

\q1

12:
Persist in casting your spells and your many sorceries\q1 which you have faithfully recited since your childhood;
\q1 perhaps you will be successful, perhaps you will scare away disaster.

\q1
